attachments.title: Hack the Dot Portland
attachments.text: Hack the Dot Portland The abusrdly awesome domain-driven hackathon @ Quick Left Portland. Want to support Hack the Dot? Click here to let us know! How the heck does this hackathon work? All the teams are told a single premium domain name at the beginning of the event to build something for. The teams then have two hours to come up with a functioning site inspired by that domain. Which ever team builds the most creative, funny, andfunctional idea for the domain wins. Participants will be judged on functionality, design, humor, and creative domain name interpretation. Learn more here: <https://hackthedot.bowtied.io/events/portland/> What you get at the event: FOOD!!!! BEER AND WINE!!!! Swag from the awesome sponsors! How much does it cost? It's free! You will also get food, drinks, and swag. Sponsors & Supporters: <http://name.com|name.com> - the domain names. QuickLeft - the event venue. Base Camp Brewing - the beer. You? Click here for info. Questions? Send them at Alex Kehr on Twitter or LinkedIn.

text: as a person who has bought every type of domain name possible and tried to come up with ideas around them, this could be really fun.
